The South African Guild of Motoring Journalists (SAGMJ) has announced its 2021 car of the year finalists across nine different categories. Besides the overall winner’s crown, the finalists can also win one of nine categories: Budget
Compact
Family Compact
Family
Premium
Performance
New Energy
Adventure SUV
Double Cab Hyundai and Toyota currently lead the rankings with each boasting four models on the finalist list. Mercedes-Benz, Porsche and Suzuki have two finalists each. The SAGMJ said that the Compact Family category is expected to be the most competitive, with different finalists this year. However, no vehicles were chosen for the Luxury category. “The final round of scoring will commence shortly and continue until 11 June 2021, where far more detailed scoring will be done on the vehicles. This round of scoring also includes automated factors based on sales data,” it said. Below are the full list of finalists in each major category. Budget <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-382895" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/S-Presso-5.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="667" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/S-Presso-5.jpg 1000w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/S-Presso-5-300x200.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/S-Presso-5-768x512.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> Hyundai Grand i10
